        <div id='help' class='cta'>
	  Definitions:
	  <ul>
	    <li><b>Newest best stories</b> - is average of 15 newest stories on the HN home page, this measures how new are the stories on the first page and how many "up-voters" are currently clicking. </li>
	    <li><b>Oldest new stories</b> - is average of 15 oldest stories on the HN newest page, this measures how many new competing stories there are and how many "submitters" are currently sending. </li>
	    <li><b>Pickup ratio</b> - is equal to <i>Newest best stories</i> minus <i>Oldest new stories</i>, this measures what is your chance of getting to the first page. You want a lot of "up-voters" and very few "submitters". </li>
	    <li><b>Now it's ... time</b> - gives four recommendation based on four quantiles of <i>Pickup ratio</i> values that are gathered over many days from HN. </li>
	  </ul>
	  Data Mining provides quantiles (percentiles). Based on three quantiles system generates four recommendations for submitting new story: <i>very good</i>, <i>good</i>, <i>so-so</i>, and <i>bad</i>.
